fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Given a diagram D, the cone functor C^\text {op}\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{Cone}_F}
Set is the functor C^\text {op}\xrightarrow {\Delta }C^J^\text {op}\xrightarrow {\operatorname {Hom}(-, F)}\operatorname {Set}, where \Delta  embeds objects
as the appropriate constant functors.

First, we claim that the map        \begin {aligned}       \Phi  \colon  \hat {C}(yA, F) &\to  FA\\             \alpha  &\mapsto  \alpha _A(1_A)       \end {aligned}     
    is a bijection. The inverse        \Psi  \colon  FA \to  \hat {C}(yA, F)     sends any x\in  FA to the natural transformation with components        \Psi  x_B: C(B,A)\to  FB,\quad  f\mapsto  Ff(x).     
