  }


      \begin {tikzcd}
        \alpha \ar [dd, mapsto, "\beta _*"']\ar [r, mapsto, "\Phi _F"] & \alpha _A(1_A) \ar [d, mapsto, "\beta _A"] \\
                                                                   & \beta _A(\alpha _A(1_A)) \\
        \beta \alpha \ar [r, mapsto, "\Psi _G"'] & (\beta \alpha )_A(1_A)\ar [u, equals]\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
      \end {tikzcd}

Finally, naturality in A asserts that, given A\xleftarrow {f} B, 




